summary: This is a sealed document tracking form from the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of Florida, filed by the U.S. Attorney's Office in West Palm Beach. It pertains to grand jury subpoenas duces tecum numbers OLY-63 and OLY-64 in case FGJ 07-103, and the government is requesting the documents remain sealed under Federal Rule of Criminal Procedure 6(e).

events.title: Filing of Sealed Grand Jury Documents
events.description: The U.S. Attorney's Office filed a motion to keep documents related to grand jury subpoenas OLY-63 and OLY-64 under seal.

locations: United States District Court Southern District of Florida
keyFacts: The document is a sealed document tracking form from the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of Florida.
It relates to grand jury subpoenas duces tecum numbers OLY-63 and OLY-64 in case FGJ 07-103 (WPB).
The U.S. Attorney's Office in West Palm Beach filed it on August 31, 2007.
The government is requesting the documents remain sealed under Federal Rule of Criminal Procedure 6(e), which governs grand jury secrecy.
The form indicates the matter should remain sealed until the conclusion of the case or permanently.
